Now, I'm pretty confident that this is a server-side issue. I'm posting it here in case I'm wrong as Azure's support told me to. The code I'm using to call the Azure SDK hasn't changed in some time; the error is somewhat error and seems to randomly happen. I think this supports my idea of a server-side issue - would anyone mind confirming my suspicions? If not, I'm happy to provide more detail.

The `custom.css` file allows to customise each and every aspect of a notebook. I have put my own modifications in the .css file but I'm unable to find the specific class that pertains to code snippets within markdown cells. That is `a snippet` inserted through the usual back-ticks.

Inspecting in Chrome shows a long chain of properties for snippets that are mostly identical to the whole markdown cell properties thus making them indistinguishable. I was assuming that setting text_cell_render to 11 points should result in code snippets displaying in the same size but close observation tells me there's a difference.

    /* Change rendered font */
    div.text_cell_render {
      font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;
      font-size: 11pt;
    }
Is there a property similar to above where I can change properties of code rendered within markdown cells?

For example, we have the following:

```python
class Entity(Model):
    parameter = StringType()

    @serializable(type=URLType)
    def entity_url(self, **kwargs)
        context = kwargs.get('context')
        if context and self.parameter is not None:
            request = context['request']  # context is a dict with 'request' key
            entity_route = request.app.route['entities']  # aiohttp-like router, for example
            return entity_route.url_for(parameter=self.parameter)
```

So, this is will not to work, because of no any keyword arguments (there is `context` might be) passed to Serializable type instance. Serializable getter (`fget`) receive only instance of model as argument. Is any way to doing something like this? How to make serializable field context aware?

P.S. I am use fork of Schematics with manually merged #466.

I've updated to the .NET Core 2.1 preview in order to make an SSL connection. Our server requires an ALPN negotiation to occur. As I understand it, the preview is the first version of .NET Core to support ALPN.

Here is essentially what I'm doing:

``` 
TcpClient tcpClient = new TcpClient();
